  "root_text": {
    "iti28:0.1": "Itivuttaka 28 ",
    "iti28:0.2": "Dukanipāta ",
    "iti28:0.3": "Paṭhamavagga ",
    "iti28:0.4": "Dukkhavihārasutta ",
    "iti28:1.1": "(…) Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti28:2.1": "“Dvīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhaṁ viharati savighātaṁ saupāyāsaṁ sapariḷāhaṁ; ",
    "iti28:2.2": "kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā. ",
    "iti28:2.3": "Katamehi dvīhi? ",
    "iti28:2.4": "Indriyesu aguttadvāratāya ca, bhojane amattaññutāya ca. ",
    "iti28:2.5": "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dvīhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhaṁ viharati savighātaṁ saupāyāsaṁ sapariḷāhaṁ; ",
    "iti28:2.6": "kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā”ti. ",
    "iti28:2.7": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti28:2.8": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti28:3.1": "“Cakkhu sotañca ghānañca, ",
    "iti28:3.2": "jivhā kāyo tathā mano; ",
    "iti28:3.3": "Etāni yassa dvārāni, ",
    "iti28:3.4": "aguttāni ca bhikkhuno. ",
    "iti28:4.1": "Bhojanamhi amattaññū, ",
    "iti28:4.2": "indriyesu asaṁvuto; ",
    "iti28:4.3": "Kāyadukkhaṁ cetodukkhaṁ, ",
    "iti28:4.4": "dukkhaṁ so adhigacchati. ",
    "iti28:5.1": "Ḍayhamānena kāyena, ",
    "iti28:5.2": "Ḍayhamānena cetasā; ",
    "iti28:5.3": "Divā vā yadi vā rattiṁ, ",
    "iti28:5.4": "Dukkhaṁ viharati tādiso”ti. ",
    "iti28:6.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti28:6.2": "Paṭhamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti28:0.1": "So It Was Said 28 ",
    "iti28:0.2": "The Book of the Twos ",
    "iti28:0.3": "Chapter One ",
    "iti28:0.4": "Living in Suffering ",
    "iti28:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti28:2.1": "“Mendicants, when a mendicant has two qualities they live unhappily in this very life—with distress, anguish, and fever—",
    "iti28:2.2": "and when the body breaks up, after death, they can expect a bad rebirth. ",
    "iti28:2.3": "What two? ",
    "iti28:2.4": "Not guarding the sense doors and eating too much. ",
    "iti28:2.5": "When a mendicant possesses these two qualities they live unhappily in this very life—with distress, anguish, and fever—",
    "iti28:2.6": "and when the body breaks up, after death, they can expect a bad rebirth.” ",
    "iti28:2.7": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti28:2.8": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti28:3.1": "“Eye, ear, nose, ",
    "iti28:3.2": "tongue, body, and likewise mind: ",
    "iti28:3.3": "a mendicant who leaves these ",
    "iti28:3.4": "sense doors unguarded—",
    "iti28:4.1": "immoderate in eating, ",
    "iti28:4.2": "sense faculties unrestrained—",
    "iti28:4.3": "reaps suffering ",
    "iti28:4.4": "both physical and mental. ",
    "iti28:5.1": "Burning in body, ",
    "iti28:5.2": "burning in mind, ",
    "iti28:5.3": "by day or by night ",
    "iti28:5.4": "such a person lives in suffering.” ",
    "iti28:6.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti28:1.1": "(…) → (dve dhamme anukkaṭi) (csp1ed) ",
    "iti28:2.4": "aguttadvāratāya → aguttadvāro (aṭṭha.) | amattaññutāya → amattaññū (aṭṭha.) ",
    "iti28:3.4": "aguttāni ca → aguttānīdha (bj); aguttānidha (pts-vp-pli1, csp1ed) "
  },
